Paris Saint-Germain manager, Mauricio Pochettino has criticized his players following their Champions League 3-1 defeat against Real Madrid on Wednesday night in Spain. Pochettino said his players were exposed during the encounter, adding that they didn’t manage their emotions well. A hat-trick from Karim Benzema ensured Real Madrid defeated PSG at the Santiago Bernabeu. Kylian Mbappe did score for PSG, but the French Ligue 1 giants were unable to progress to the next round after losing 3-2 on aggregate. Speaking after the game, Pochettino said at his post-match press conference: “We didn’t manage our emotions well. “We left ourselves exposed. We leave with great pain and disappointment because we didn’t score the goals to reflect our superiority over the two games.”